        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gitlab): add GitLab provider support",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds GitLab as a supported hosting provider alongside GitHub, including GitLab.com and self-managed GitLab instances.\r\n\r\n## What changed\r\n\r\n- Added provider-aware account handling with `HostingProvider` support for GitHub and GitLab.\r\n- Added GitLab PAT authentication using GitLab REST API and `PRIVATE-TOKEN`.\r\n- Added `GitLabClient` and GitLab response models for:\r\n  - projects\r\n  - issues\r\n  - merge requests\r\n  - CI/CD jobs\r\n  - releases\r\n  - tags\r\n  - branches\r\n  - contributors\r\n  - commits\r\n- Updated app refresh, repository browsing, recent lists, and pinned repo loading to use the active provider client.\r\n- Updated settings UI so users can add a GitLab account with a GitLab base URL and PAT scopes: `read_user`, `read_api`, `read_repository`.\r\n- Updated menu labels and repository URLs for GitLab, including merge requests and CI/CD jobs paths.\r\n- Added CLI support for GitLab login and provider-aware repo commands:\r\n  - `repobar login --provider gitlab --host https://gitlab.com --token glpat-...`\r\n- Preserved GitHub-only behavior for GitHub App OAuth, GitHub diagnostics, traffic stats, contribution heatmaps, release/PR notifications, and archive fallback.\r\n- Updated README to document GitLab support and current feature boundaries.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\nAdded coverage for GitLab account models, PAT authentication, REST API mapping, provider client selection, GitLab URL building, menu labels, workflow job rendering, and CLI repo parsing.",
